Peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop a #deep saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting lid) on medium heat with half the @Butter{10%g}.

When melted, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%secs}. Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} until coated, ~{1%min}. Add 1/4 tsp @salt{}, some @Water for the Rice{300%ml} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Pickled Radishes ==

While the rice cooks, thinly slice the @Radishes{100%g}(thinly sliced).

Pop the radishes into a #small bowl{} and add the @Rice Vinegar{22%ml} and @Sugar{1%tsp for the Pickle}. Add a pinch of @salt{}, mix together and set aside. Set aside to pickle.

== Ginger Mushrooms ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

When hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%mins}.

Drain the @Firm Tofu{280%g} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Add the tofu to a #medium bowl{} with the @Cornflour{20%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Set aside for now.

Once the mushrooms have browned, reduce the heat to medium, then add the @Ginger Puree{15%g} and remaining @Butter{10%g} to the pan.

Fry until the ginger is fragrant and the butter has melted, ~{1%min}.

Transfer the ginger mushrooms to a medium bowl and cover with a lid or #foil{} to keep warm.

== Honey-Gochujang Tofu ==

Carefully wipe out the (now empty) #frying pan{} and return to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the tofu and fry until golden, ~{8-10%mins}. Turn frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.

Reduce the heat to medium, then stir in the @Gochujang Paste{50%g}, @Honey{15%g} and @Water for the Sauce{75%ml}. Stir frequently until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{1-2%mins}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

== Assembly ==

Stir the pickling liquid from the radishes through the rice and fluff it up with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the honey-gochujang tofu, ginger mushrooms and pickled radishes in separate sections.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} to finish.

Enjoy!